%N A183655 Number of (n+1) X 3 0..5 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 10.
%H A183655 Zhuorui He, <a href="/A183655/b183655.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a> (first 200 terms from R. H. Hardin)
%H A183655 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183655/a183655.txt">Proof of formulas</a>, Jun 12 2026.
%H A183655 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (21,-175,735,-1624,1764,-720).
%F A183655 a(n) = 21*a(n-1) - 175*a(n-2) + 735*a(n-3) - 1624*a(n-4) + 1764*a(n-5) - 720*a(n-6).
%F A183655 G.f.: 6*x*(111 - 1924*x + 12543*x^2 - 37994*x^3 + 52584*x^4 - 25920*x^5) / ((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)*(1 - 5*x)*(1 - 6*x)). - _Colin Barker_, Apr 02 2018
%F A183655 a(n) = 6*6^n + 30*5^n + 48*4^n + 54*3^n + 48*2^n + 30. - _Christian Krause_, Jun 12 2026
%e A183655 Some solutions for 5 X 3:
%e A183655 ..5..0..5....2..1..1....1..4..1....1..5..1....4..1..1....2..3..5....3..0..3
